==Trivia==
*In the comics, Samuel Sterns was a menial laborer with only average intelligence. Upon being exposed to [[gamma radiation]] while he was transporting hazardous materials, he became the evil super-genius known as the Leader. Sterns was also the founder and leader of the [[Intelligencia]], a group comprised of the smartest super-villains in the Marvel Universe.
**He bears some resemblance to his brother, [[w:c:marvel:Madman|Phillip "Phil" Sterns]], a scientist who studied gamma radiation and romanticized the concept of the Hulk before eventually receiving gamma-based powers himself.
**His online name "Mr. Blue" was used in the comics as an alias used by [[Betty Ross]].
***As a reference to the nickname "Mr. Blue", Sterns uses [[The Fleetwoods]]' song "{{WPS|Mr. Blue}}" to brainwash individuals.

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Aaron Sims]] produced concept art of the Leader for ''[[The Incredible Hulk]]'' although Samuel Sterns does not fully transform into the Leader during the film.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20081014234450/http://www.xsibase.com/articles.php?detail=147 Designing the Incredible Hulk]</ref>
*Director [[Louis Leterrier]] introduced Samuel Sterns in ''[[The Incredible Hulk]]'' with the intention to set him up to become the main antagonist as the Leader in a possible sequel.<ref>[http://www.mtv.com/news/2593169/tim-blake-nelson-will-battle-hulk-as-the-leader-in-incredible-hulk-2-with-or-without-ed-norton/ TIM BLAKE NELSON WILL BATTLE HULK AS 'THE LEADER' IN 'INCREDIBLE HULK 2’ -- WITH OR WITHOUT ED NORTON]</ref> [[Tim Blake Nelson]] even "signed on" to reprise his role in two more films.<ref>[http://www.mtv.com/news/1589158/incredible-hulk-stars-director-already-have-wish-list-for-hulk-2-iron-man-samson-the-leader-and-more/ 'INCREDIBLE HULK' STARS, DIRECTOR ALREADY HAVE WISH LIST FOR 'HULK 2': IRON MAN, SAMSON, THE LEADER AND MORE]</ref>
*The Leader coming back in ''[[Captain America: Brave New World]]'' was one of the main reasons that attracted [[Julius Onah]] to the project.<ref>[https://comicbook.com/marvel/news/captain-america-new-world-order-director-confirms-leader-villain-exclusive/ Captain America: New World Order Director Confirms Marvel Movie's Villain (Exclusive)]</ref>
*''[[She-Hulk: Attorney at Law]]'' head writer [[Jessica Gao (writer)|Jessica Gao]]'s original 2019 pitch for the show's [[She-Hulk: Attorney at Law/Season One|first season]] had the Leader having a substantial role in the story, though there were discussions about either bringing Samuel Sterns back or have a new version of the Leader appear that could or could not have been related to Sterns. Gao does not quite remember why the Leader's inclusion was scrapped.<ref>[https://comicbook.com/tv-shows/news/she-hulk-the-leader-season-1-scrapped-jessica-gao-spoilers-exclusive/ She-Hulk: The Leader Was Originally Part of Season 1 Plans (Exclusive)]</ref>
*In the original cut of ''[[Captain America: Brave New World]]'', Sterns was depicted with an appearance based on the traditional look of the Leader in the comics, with a smooth, enlarged head and facial hair.<ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/DImt_LPv4eZ/?utm_source=ig_embed&img_index=1</ref> This appearance was discarded in the film's reshoots and changed to the one featured in the final cut.
*[[Scotty Cook]] was a stunt double for [[Tim Blake Nelson]] in the role of Samuel Sterns.

